      "outcome": "The Silent Spire Keepers successfully establish a covert early-warning network along the canal approach. Three sentinel posts — staffed by monastic listeners trained in the Unspoken Tongue's interpretive framework — now monitor all traffic approaching the Spire. The posts are camouflaged as simple devotional waypoints, indistinguishable from the canal's existing religious infrastructure. Within days, the sentinels detect and log the acoustic signatures of several Signal-House gondola couriers carrying quadruple-authenticated lacquer seals, confirming the Families' expanding technological reach toward the Spire's waters. The Keepers now have advance warning of any attempt to install monitoring equipment, and the acoustic jamming arrays can be calibrated to counter specific signal frequencies observed in the field. The Council's delegation route is also now under passive surveillance — the Keepers know exactly who approaches and what they carry. The Spire's isolation remains intact, but its defensive awareness now extends far beyond its walls.",
